snippet: Ron Barber, who also survived the shooting that injured Gabrielle Giffords, will have to run again in November.
abstract: Ron Barber defeats Republican rival Jesse Kelly in the closely contested race to finish Gabrielle Giffords's third term in Congress; Barber, a survivor of the shooting rampage that ended Giffords's career, takes 52 percent of the vote.

byline.original: By SARAH GARRECHT GASSEN and FERNANDA SANTOS
byline.contributor: Sarah Garrecht Gassen reported from Tucson, and Fernanda Santos from Phoenix.

lead_paragraph: Ron Barber, who also survived the shooting that injured Gabrielle Giffords, will have to run again in November.

headline.seo: Former Aide to Giffords Wins Her Seat
headline.main: Aide to Giffords Is Elected to Finish Unexpired Term
headline.print_headline: Aide to Giffords Is Elected To Finish Unexpired Term
